This paper discusses the detection of e-crime, specifically the exploitation of URL shorteners, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves analyzing a large dataset, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or social media (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of features to classify URLs as malicious or benign, which could fall under the sub-categories of cybercrime (cs.CY) or multimedia (cs.MM).
